<sect1 id="Layout.GEM">
	<title>Gem</title>
	<para>
		The
		<ulink
			url="http://digbib.ubka.uni-karlsruhe.de/volltexte/documents/765878">
			<citetitle>GEM Algorithm</citetitle>
		</ulink>
		is based on the spring-embedder paradigm.
	</para>
	<para>
		<screenshot>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="../images/layout/layout_GEM1.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</screenshot>
	</para>
	<para>
		The results shows clusters of connected concepts.
	</para>
	<para>
		<screenshot>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="../images/layout/layout_GEM2.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</screenshot>
	</para>
	<para>
		One can zoom in and study clusters in more details.
	</para>
	<para>
		<screenshot>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="../images/layout/layout_GEM3.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</screenshot>
	</para>
	<para>
		It is also possible to arrange the clusters in a rectangle shape
		sorted by cluster size to obtain a better overview of the graph.
	</para>
	<para>
		<screenshot>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="../images/layout/layout_GEM4.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</screenshot>
	</para>
</sect1>